        "faq_1": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is the recorder accurate for Arabic and English?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes — 98%+ accuracy in both Arabic and English, with 134 languages supported in total. It handles code-switching (mixing Arabic and English mid-sentence) better than any recorder we've tested. Works across all UAE dialects including Gulf, Levantine, and Egyptian Arabic.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_2": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How long does the battery last?",
            "answer": "<p>20+ hours of continuous recording. Charge it once and record all week — no interruptions to your workflow.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_3": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Does it transcribe meetings automatically?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes — press record and walk into any meeting. When you stop, the AI summary is ready: key points, decisions and action items all extracted for you.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_4": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is it secure for business and client work?",
            "answer": "<p>All recordings are encrypted end-to-end. Nothing is shared with third parties without your explicit consent — safe for confidential meetings and legal consultations.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_5": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Do you deliver to Abu Dhabi, Sharjah & other emirates?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes! TipTop360 delivers free to all UAE emirates — Dubai, Abu Dhabi, Sharjah, Ajman, RAK, Fujairah & Umm Al Quwain. Cash on Delivery available everywhere. Order before 8 PM for next-day delivery in major cities.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_6": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How does aiVox compare to Plaud Note and other AI recorders?",
            "answer": "<p>aiVox offers comparable GPT-4 transcription accuracy to Plaud Note at a significantly lower price (Dhs. 450 vs Dhs. 500–700). TipTop360 customers get 1 year of unlimited transcription free, then 400 minutes per month at no extra cost. Plus free next-day delivery across the UAE, cash on delivery, and local customer support. No subscription required.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_7": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How much does the AI voice recorder cost in UAE?",
            "answer": "<p>The aiVox GPT-4 AI Voice Recorder costs <strong>Dhs. 450</strong> at TipTop360 — including 1 year of unlimited transcription free. Comparable devices like Plaud Note retail for Dhs. 600–700 and require paid subscriptions. Free next-day delivery and Cash on Delivery available across all 7 UAE emirates.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_8": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can it transcribe Arabic meetings accurately?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes — the aiVox achieves <strong>98% transcription accuracy in Arabic</strong>, including Gulf, Levantine, and Egyptian dialects. It handles Arabic-English code-switching natively, making it ideal for UAE business meetings where both languages are used interchangeably. No manual language selection needed — the AI detects and transcribes automatically.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_9": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "AI voice recorder vs phone recording app — which is better?",
            "answer": "<p><strong>Dedicated AI recorders outperform phone apps</strong> in three critical ways: (1) Dual-microphone hardware captures voices across an entire meeting room — phones only pick up nearby speakers. (2) 20+ hour battery vs draining your phone battery during long sessions. (3) Purpose-built GPT-4 processing delivers 98% accuracy vs phone apps that average 80–85%. The aiVox also keeps recordings separate from your personal device for privacy and compliance.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_10": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is it legal to record meetings and conversations in the UAE?",
            "answer": "<p>In the UAE, recording is generally permitted with <strong>consent of the participants</strong>. For business meetings, informing attendees that the meeting is being recorded is standard professional practice. The aiVox uses end-to-end AES-256 encryption to protect all recordings, meeting UAE data privacy expectations. Always check your organisation's recording policy and obtain verbal consent before recording confidential or legal proceedings.</p>"
          }
        },
