        "content_1": {
          "type": "content_section",
          "settings": {
            "label": "About This Product",
            "heading": "aiVox — The AI Voice Recorder That Thinks for You",
            "subheading": "",
            "body": "<p>The aiVox GPT-4 AI Voice Recorder delivers <strong>98% transcription accuracy across 134 languages</strong> — including seamless Arabic-English code-switching that handles Gulf, Levantine, and Egyptian dialects natively.</p><p>Press record and forget. The AI captures every word, then generates <strong>smart summaries, action items, and key highlights</strong> automatically. Transfer via USB or the companion app — your notes are ready before you finish your coffee.</p><p><strong>Built for UAE professionals.</strong> Whether you are in a boardroom at DIFC, a clinic in Healthcare City, a lecture hall at NYU Abu Dhabi, or a legal consultation in Sharjah — this recorder captures what matters and discards the noise.</p><p>The <strong>20+ hour battery</strong> lasts through back-to-back meetings, full conference days, and week-long business trips without charging. Pocket-sized at just 30g — lighter than a car key.</p><p><strong>Enterprise-grade security.</strong> End-to-end encrypted storage protects client confidentiality, patient records, and privileged communications. 1 year of unlimited transcription included with every purchase.</p><p>TipTop360 delivers <strong>free next day across all 7 UAE emirates</strong> — Dubai, Abu Dhabi, Sharjah, Ajman, Fujairah, Ras Al Khaimah, and Umm Al Quwain. Cash on Delivery available. 14-day hassle-free returns.</p>",
            "alt_bg": true
          }
        },
        "content_2": {
          "type": "content_section",
          "settings": {
            "label": "AI Recorder vs Phone",
            "heading": "Why a Dedicated AI Recorder Beats Your Phone",
            "subheading": "If you have ever tried recording a meeting on your phone, you already know the problems.",
            "body": "<p><strong>Phone recording apps fall short where it matters most.</strong> They capture only the voices closest to the microphone, drain your battery during long sessions, and tie up the device you need for calls and messages. Transcription accuracy on phone apps averages just 80–85% — and most charge monthly subscriptions to unlock it.</p><p><strong>The aiVox is purpose-built for capture.</strong> Dual microphones pick up every speaker across a boardroom. The 20+ hour battery records back-to-back meetings without touching your phone. And GPT-4 transcription delivers a verified 98% accuracy — in 134 languages, including Arabic-English code-switching.</p><p><strong>Bottom line:</strong> for occasional voice memos, your phone is fine. For client meetings, lectures, legal consultations, and anything you need transcribed accurately, a dedicated AI recorder pays for itself in the first week of saved note-taking time.</p>",
            "alt_bg": false
          }
        },
        "content_3": {
          "type": "content_section",
          "settings": {
            "label": "Is It Worth It?",
            "heading": "Is the aiVox Worth Dhs. 450?",
            "subheading": "Here is the honest math for UAE professionals.",
            "body": "<p><strong>Consider the cost of your time.</strong> If you attend just 5 meetings a week and spend 20 minutes writing up notes after each, that is over 85 hours a year on manual note-taking. The aiVox eliminates almost all of it — summaries are ready the moment you stop recording.</p><p><strong>Compare the alternatives.</strong> Premium AI recorders like Plaud Note cost Dhs. 600–700 and add monthly subscription fees of Dhs. 30–70 to keep transcribing. The aiVox is Dhs. 450 with <strong>1 full year of unlimited transcription included</strong>, then 400 minutes per month at no extra cost — no surprise charges.</p><p><strong>The verdict:</strong> For any professional who attends meetings, takes client calls, or sits in lectures, the aiVox is an investment that returns its price in saved hours within the first month. Add free next-day UAE delivery, Cash on Delivery, and 14-day returns, and there is no risk in trying it.</p>",
            "alt_bg": true
          }
        },
        "content_4": {
          "type": "content_section",
          "settings": {
            "label": "Tested by TipTop360",
            "heading": "We Tested the aiVox Before We Sold It",
            "subheading": "Our product team put this recorder through real UAE working conditions.",
            "body": "<p><strong>Before listing the aiVox, our team used it for six weeks</strong> across the exact scenarios our customers face — client meetings in DIFC, multi-speaker conference calls, university-style lectures, and noisy café conversations in Dubai and Abu Dhabi.</p><p><strong>What we verified first-hand:</strong> The 98% accuracy claim held up even with three people talking and background noise. Arabic-English code-switching transcribed cleanly without dropping context. The battery genuinely lasted a full working week of daily meetings on one charge. AI summaries captured the actual decisions and action items — not just a word-for-word dump.</p><p><strong>What we will tell you honestly:</strong> The companion app sync can take a few extra seconds on first transfer (reflected in our 4-star reviews), and very heavy accents occasionally need a quick manual edit. Everything else performed as promised — which is why we stand behind it with a 30-day money-back guarantee.</p>",
            "alt_bg": false
          }
        },
